Sentencas: In this paper, an integration design of membrane electrode assemblies in low temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LTSOFCs) is accomplished by using a mixed ionic-electronic conductor.
Titulo: Integration design of membrane electrode assemblies in low temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The mixed ionic-electronic conductor is a composite material, LiNiCuZn oxides, Gd2O3 and Sm-doped CeO2 composited with Na2CO3 (LiNiCuZn oxides-NGSDC), which consists of ionic conductor, n-type and p-type semiconductors.
Titulo: Integration design of membrane electrode assemblies in low temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The multi-phase composite material can also be used in single layer fuel cell (SLFC) to replace single-phase materials.
Titulo: Integration design of membrane electrode assemblies in low temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A SLFC using the LiNiCuZn oxides-NSGDC composite exhibits an OCV of 1.05 V and maximum power density of 800 mW cm(-2), which is comparable to the cell performance of conventional LTSOFCs and much higher than that of SLFC reported before.
Titulo: Integration design of membrane electrode assemblies in low temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The reasons leading to the good performance are porous structure of electrode and the matching of ionic conductor and semiconductor.
Titulo: Integration design of membrane electrode assemblies in low temperature solid oxide fuel cell
